basel_Aaa: Eagle with Basel Crosier, Single-Headed, A.a.a.

Watermark A.a.a. is distinguishable by these three features: wings that point downward, a smooth neck without ruffles, and four claws extending from the foot (marked with red).

________________________________________________________________________

This watermark can be found on the following prints:

  • The third oriental head, 1635, Rijksprentenkabinet, Amsterdam.
  • The great Jewish bride, 1635, National Gallery of Art, Washington.

(Erik Hinterding, Rembrandt as an Etcher, 2006, II, 106)
